Detailed Description

This class reperesents a trace (or beam) through a map.

This class records all cells touched by a beam through a map, starting at a point (x, y) in the some direct, using instances of MapStoreCell.

This class' primariy use is as result of a call to MapStore::trace().

Member Typedef Documentation

typedef std::list<MapStoreCell>::iterator mapstore::MapStoreTrace::MapIt

Public iterator type to walk through the trace.

This iterator allows one to access all cells in the trace one by one.

MapStore mapstore;
// ... do something with the map store ...
// obtain a trace
MapStoreTrace mst = mapstore.trace(...);
// walk the trace
MapIt myIterator = mst.traceStart();
MapIt myEnd = mst.traceEnd();
while (myIterator != myEnd) {
MapStoreCell msc = *myIterator;
myIterator++;
// ... do something with the cell ...
printf("cell (%d, %d) has value %f\n", msc.x, msc.y, msc.val);
}

Not to be confused with MapStore::MapIt.

Member Function Documentation

void MapStoreTrace::add ( const MapStoreCell &  c)

Add a cell to the trace.

Cells must be added in the correct order, i.e. in the order a beam / trace would touche the cells!

The supplied MapStoreCell instance is copied and can be reused to add another cell or can be destroyed.
